Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,WILDFIRE — Wildland Incident Locator. From a NASA satellite ping to a\Nbase-wide evacuation order in 90 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.15,0:00:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,LOGCOM Installation Incident Response challenge — MARADMIN 131/26.\NCamp Pendleton has burned six times in the last decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.65,0:00:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We pull 200 NASA FIRMS pixels biased near western Marine bases. T\Nminus six hours: every base is CLEAR.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.66,0:00:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweep the timeline forward six hours. Fires grow. The alert ladder\Nticks: WATCH, ALERT, WARNING.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.87,0:00:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Three Pendleton fires within 12 miles. Wind alignment 0.74 — Santa Ana\Nblowing the fire straight at family housing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.37,0:00:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One click. The Kamiwaza-deployed model drafts four channels at once:\NMARFORRES email, intranet banner, commander SMS, evacuation brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:01:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Each channel uses the right military register — formal email, terse\NSMS, banner ready to push.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.15,0:01:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kamiwaza-deployed model runs inside your accredited environment.\NSet KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and the entire pipeline stays on-base.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.66,0:01:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,WILDFIRE — Powered by the Kamiwaza-deployed model stack. Deploy in\Nhours, not months. 100 percent data containment.
